The NSA whistleblower [Edward Snowden](http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/jun/09/nsa-whistleblower-edward-snowden-why) leaked a set of documents to The Guardian and the Washington Post, making a worldwide scandal by giving formal evidence of the massive surveillance performed by the NSA on citizens all around the world through the PRISM program. Among the released information, we find:

- a [set of slides](http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/special/politics/prism-collection-documents/) showing that NSA's mass surveillance method consists in directly collecting data from the main US-based online service providers (Google, Microsoft, Yahoo, Apple, ...);
- [explanations and screenshots](http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/interactive/2013/jun/08/nsa-boundless-informant-data-mining-slides) of NSA's software _Boundless Informant_ allowing agents to visualize per-country statistics on data collected by PRISM.

Some reactions I saw seem to me lacking sense of reality both in the interpretation of these revelations and in how to turn away from the massive surveillance system. Here is why.

